&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;StackCommerce is the leading content-driven commerce platform, seamlessly connecting brands with engaged audiences across the full customer journey. Our unmatched network comprises over 2,500 brands, 8,000 creators, and thousands of world-renowned media outlets — including Hearst, Gannett, Ziff Davis, G/O Media, News Corp, Dotdash Meredith, Foundry, and more — as well as our owned-and-operated marketplace, StackSocial, which brings exclusive deals directly to millions of consumers. A TPG portfolio company, StackCommerce has expanded its ecosystem through the acquisitions of BrandCycle, The Fascination, and Reviewed. Learn more at StackCommerce.com.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Account Manager to join our company for a 100% remote position. The Account Manager will support our portfolio of media clients and be responsible for managing content &amp;amp; marketing campaigns across both brand and publisher teams. The ideal candidate has direct client service experience and a proven track record managing large-performance marketing campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Execution: &lt;/strong&gt;Acts as the main point of contact for sold content campaigns, managing day to day tasks to ensure program success and positive client relationships. Proactively identifies and removes any roadblocks that prevent goals from being met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Manages the full lifecycle of content campaigns. This would include owning the agenda for kick off calls, managing all client and partner deliverables, setting and meeting deadlines, communicating progress across all stakeholders, and ensuring a successful launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Campaign Optimization: &lt;/strong&gt;While campaign launch will be the Account Manager’s responsibility, post launch responsibilities include monitoring reporting and utilizing metrics to optimize active campaigns with publisher clients, ensuring accountability for performance and maximizing overall results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of online marketing, e-commerce, or affiliate marketing experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Affiliate Marketing and Networks (ShareASale, Commission Junction, Impact, Rakuten, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of basic media buying on social and programmatic platforms &amp;amp; whitelisting SOPs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel/ sheet capabilities and comfortable with formatting, formulas, customizing reports, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has successfully worked in a client-facing role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate is:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides unsurpassed customer service leading to long-lasting customer relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong internal motivation to get the job done and done well&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possesses excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emphasizes an incredible attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrives in a fast-paced environment and enjoys bringing order to chaos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritizes competing objectives and manages time with skill&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Displays accountability always meeting deadlines and keeping commitments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoys working autonomously and is driven by clear goals and objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knows how to collaborate with team members in a remote environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
