&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BrandCycle is an influencer and affiliate marketing platform representing over 7,000 social media influencers, bloggers, and content creators. Our members have a combined following of more than 300 million on social media. Most of our influencers have been creating content to drive sales for years. They are savvy shoppers who cross-promote and achieve high ROI for brands. We work with over 700 top brands, including Target, lululemon, Michael Kors, Under Armour, Crocs, Kate Spade, and Converse. In 2021, BrandCycle was acquired by StackCommerce, a leader in commerce content for major digital media publishers. StackCommerce and BrandCycle are backed by TPG, a top private equity firm that is known for its growth equity and impact investing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring a Creator Partnerships Manager to lead the strategic management and growth of our top-earning creators. You’ll be the primary relationship owner for a portfolio of creators — a trusted partner who maximizes their earnings, deepens their engagement, and champions their needs across the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role blends high-touch partnership with scalable strategy. You’ll deliver best-in-class support and guidance while working closely with our Brand, Influencer, Product, and Data teams to meet creators’ current and future needs. Above all, you’ll represent the voice of the creator. It’s a great opportunity to join a fast-growing company at a pivotal moment in our growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own strategic creator partnerships. &lt;/strong&gt;Manage and grow a portfolio of top-tier influencers and creators, anticipating their needs and building for long-term retention and success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive performance and growth. &lt;/strong&gt;Analyze creator performance data and deliver actionable recommendations to grow earnings. Build reporting and operational resources that support both strategic planning and day-to-day execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally. &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with Brand, Influencer, Product, and Data teams to make sure creator needs are reflected in what we build and how we operate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be the voice of the creator. &lt;/strong&gt;Advocate for creators across departments and build feedback loops between creators and Product, ensuring the roadmap solves for real creator pain points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own retention metrics. &lt;/strong&gt;Take ownership of the numbers that define success, including monthly active creators, earnings growth, and creator NPS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4–6 years of experience in customer success, account management, or creator/influencer/partnership roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record managing and growing high-profile accounts or creator/influencer or publisher relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of affiliate networks, creator platforms, and social platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with AI and automation tools, and a genuine desire to expand how you use them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written, verbal, and presentation skills — you can influence and guide top-tier accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Mailchimp, HubSpot, Claude, Looker is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
